Subject: [PATCH net v3] net: gro: fix double aggregation of flush-marked skbs

skb_gro_receive_list() only refuses to coalesce when the combined length
would exceed 64 KiB, but unlike the non-list path skb_gro_receive() it
never checks NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->flush. An skb already marked for flush
(must-not-coalesce) can therefore be merged into the frag_list, producing
a doubly-aggregated super-frame with inconsistent length/checksum state.

Add the same flush guard the regular GRO path already carries, so the two
paths behave consistently and flush-marked skbs are never appended to a
frag_list.

Upstream net patch (v3). Local overlay for the W1700K 6.18 build until it
lands in a 6.18.x stable / OpenWrt master sync; drop on dedup.
---
 net/core/gro.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/core/gro.c b/net/core/gro.c
index 35f2f708f010..076247c1e662 100644
--- a/net/core/gro.c
+++ b/net/core/gro.c
@@ -229,7 +229,8 @@ int skb_gro_receive(struct sk_buff *p, struct sk_buff *skb)

 int skb_gro_receive_list(struct sk_buff *p, struct sk_buff *skb)
 {
-	if (unlikely(p->len + skb->len >= 65536))
+	if (unlikely(p->len + skb->len >= 65536 ||
+		     NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->flush))
 		return -E2BIG;

 	if (!pskb_may_pull(skb, skb_gro_offset(skb))) {
